WEBVTT

00:00.839 --> 00:02.828
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:02.828 --> 00:03.502
JUDGE CRYER.

00:03.502 --> 00:04.805
WHERE IS WYATT?
HE'S BEEN ARRESTED.

00:04.805 --> 00:06.607
I'M GOING TO GET YOU OUT.
POP!

00:06.607 --> 00:09.009
DON'T SAY A WORD TO ANYBODY,
WYATT, NOT A WORD!

00:09.009 --> 00:10.944
IS HE BREATHING?

00:10.944 --> 00:11.978
YES.

00:11.978 --> 00:13.747
YOUR WIFE HAS THE CAR.

00:13.747 --> 00:15.015
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

00:15.015 --> 00:17.317
WYATT TOLD ME HE THOUGHT
THAT YOUR WIFE TURNED IT IN.

00:17.317 --> 00:19.052
YOU HAVE HAD HIS CAR
ALL THIS TIME!

00:19.052 --> 00:20.086
WHERE IS IT?

00:20.086 --> 00:21.321
I AM NOT TELLING YOU.

00:21.321 --> 00:22.322
TALK TO ME.

00:22.322 --> 00:23.323
SHE'S NOT PREGNANT.

00:23.323 --> 00:24.324
SHE'S NOT?

00:24.324 --> 00:26.760
I WANT TO START BY SAYING

00:26.760 --> 00:30.296
THAT I HAVE BEEN PART
OF A COVERUP.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.171
MRS. CRYER?

00:38.171 --> 00:40.106
NOT NOW, CELINE.

00:40.106 --> 00:42.375
TRUST ME, YOU WANT
TO SEE THIS.

00:42.375 --> 00:43.944
I SAID NOT NOW.

00:43.944 --> 00:47.013
BUT, MA'AM...

00:47.013 --> 00:49.182
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU FOUR?

00:49.182 --> 00:51.552
I THINK YOU WANT
TO SEE THIS.

00:54.054 --> 00:57.958
<i>I'VE BEEN PART OF A COVERUP</i>
<i>AND I AM NOT PROUD OF IT.</i>

00:57.958 --> 01:01.301
<i>BUT I AM WILLING</i>
<i>TO SUFFER THE CONSEQUENCES.</i>

01:01.301 --> 01:03.704
<i>WHAT MOST OF THE PUBLIC</i>
<i>DOESN'T KNOW IS THAT</i>

01:03.704 --> 01:05.105
<i>MY SON HAS A DRUG PROBLEM,</i>

01:05.105 --> 01:09.943
<i>AND HE'S HAD ONE</i>
<i>SINCE HE WAS 16 YEARS OLD.</i>

01:09.943 --> 01:12.746
<i>KATHERYN AND I HAVE PUT</i>
<i>HIM IN SEVERAL FACILITIES</i>

01:12.746 --> 01:15.148
<i>OVER THE YEARS TRYING</i>
<i>TO GET HELP FOR HIM,</i>

01:15.148 --> 01:17.551
BUT MOST OF THOSE HAVE FAILED,

01:17.551 --> 01:20.954
LARGELY BECAUSE HE WOULDN'T
DO THE WORK.

01:20.954 --> 01:22.623
I'M NOT
PROUD OF THAT,

01:22.623 --> 01:26.192
AND I LOVE MY SON WITH ALL
MY HEART,

01:26.192 --> 01:30.531
WITH ALL MY SOUL,
BUT WHAT HE'S DONE IS WRONG.

01:30.531 --> 01:32.899
BUT LET ME MAKE THIS
VERY, VERY CLEAR.

01:32.899 --> 01:34.334
MY SON DID HIT SOMEONE,

01:34.334 --> 01:38.539
BUT HE DID NOT ‐‐ I REPEAT ‐‐
HE DID NOT HIT LIZZIE,

01:38.539 --> 01:40.707
HE DID NOT HIT BENNY YOUNG.

01:43.143 --> 01:44.545
HE DIDN'T DO IT.

01:44.545 --> 01:46.747
HE DIDN'T HIT BENNY YOUNG.
HE DID NOT HIT LITTLE LIZZIE.

01:46.747 --> 01:50.150
THE CAR HE WAS DRIVING
IS RIGHT THERE BEHIND YOU.

01:53.019 --> 01:55.622
IT'S A BLACK SEDAN, YES.

01:55.622 --> 01:59.092
AND ALSO, THE MAN
THAT HE HIT IS HERE.

01:59.092 --> 02:00.861
THIS IS DONALD LEE QUESTAL.

02:00.861 --> 02:03.870
IT'S TRUE, I DID PAY
FOR HIS MEDICAL BILLS,

02:03.870 --> 02:06.673
AND I SETTLED OUT OF COURT
WITH MR. QUESTAL.

02:06.673 --> 02:08.108
IT'S TRUE, I ASKED HIM

02:08.108 --> 02:11.277
NOT TO PRESS CHARGES.

02:11.277 --> 02:14.180
THESE ARE THINGS I'M NOT PROUD
OF, BUT THESE ARE THINGS I DID

02:14.180 --> 02:16.182
TO PROTECT MY SON.

02:16.182 --> 02:18.818
<i>AND I WANT TO MAKE THIS</i>
<i>VERY, VERY CLEAR.</i>

02:18.818 --> 02:20.286
<i>MY WIFE KATHERYN CRYER</i>

02:20.286 --> 02:22.889
<i>WAS NOT AWARE OF ANY OF THIS</i>
<i>AT ANY TIME, AT ALL.</i>

02:22.889 --> 02:26.693
<i>NOW, AS A PARENT OF A CHILD</i>
<i>THAT HAS AN ADDICTION ‐‐</i>

02:26.693 --> 02:30.463
AND I'M SURE THERE ARE MANY
OF YOU OUT THERE ‐‐

02:30.463 --> 02:34.535
MANY OF YOU WHO KNOW
THE ANGUISH OF THAT SITUATION.

02:34.535 --> 02:37.871
YOU KNOW THE CONSTANT PAIN,
YOU KNOW THE LOSS OF HOPE.

02:37.871 --> 02:39.172
YOU DO.

02:40.807 --> 02:43.343
I AM SO SORRY THAT I TRIED
TO COVER THIS UP.

02:43.343 --> 02:47.213
BUT AGAIN, I AM WILLING TO FACE
WHATEVER I HAVE TO GO THROUGH.

02:47.213 --> 02:48.381
WHATEVER IT IS.

02:48.381 --> 02:52.819
I LOVE MY CHILDREN VERY MUCH,
THAT'S TRUE.

02:52.819 --> 02:56.156
BUT IF THIS MAN HAD DIED,
OR IF MY SON

02:56.156 --> 03:00.460
HAD HIT A LITTLE GIRL...

03:00.460 --> 03:03.303
I PROMISE YOU,
I WOULD BE THE FIRST,

03:03.303 --> 03:05.471
THE VERY FIRST TO TURN HIM IN.

03:06.306 --> 03:08.141
♪♪♪♪

03:16.650 --> 03:20.086
YES, IT'S TRUE, I'M A FATHER,
BUT I'M ALSO A JUDGE.

03:20.086 --> 03:22.556
I'M A JUDGE
WHO HAS A MORAL RIGHT

03:22.556 --> 03:25.792
AND A RESPONSIBILITY TO LOOK
AFTER THE WELLBEING

03:25.792 --> 03:28.662
OF THE CITIZENS OF THIS GREAT
CITY AND THIS GREAT COUNTRY

03:28.662 --> 03:30.931
THAT WE HAVE THE GREAT FORTUNE
TO LIVE IN.

03:30.931 --> 03:34.768
I'M SORRY, AND I'M WILLING
TO DEAL DIRECTLY

03:34.768 --> 03:39.606
WITH THE D. A.'S OFFICE, BUT
AT THIS TIME, I AM REQUESTING

03:39.606 --> 03:42.475
THAT THE D. A. RELEASE MY SON
AND DROP THE CHARGES

03:42.475 --> 03:44.310
OF HITTING LIZZIE AND MR. YOUNG.

03:44.310 --> 03:48.615
BECAUSE QUITE SIMPLY,
HE DID NOT DO IT.

03:48.615 --> 03:50.851
NOW, IF THEY WANT TO BRING
CHARGES AGAINST HIM

03:50.851 --> 03:52.085
FOR THE INCIDENT AT HAND,

03:52.085 --> 03:55.455
AND THAT IS HITTING MR. QUESTAL,

03:55.455 --> 03:56.890
I WILL ACCEPT THAT.

03:56.890 --> 03:58.424
I WILL.

03:58.424 --> 04:02.168
BUT THIS WITCH HUNT BY
D. A. JENNIFER SALISON,

04:02.168 --> 04:04.671
IT'S A PERSONAL VENDETTA
AGAINST ME,

04:04.671 --> 04:08.341
AND I DO NOT BELIEVE THAT MY SON
SHOULD BE USED AS A PAWN

04:08.341 --> 04:09.743
IN ONE OF HER GAMES.

04:09.743 --> 04:13.013
PERSONALLY, I THINK
THE RESOURCES OF THE TAXPAYERS

04:13.013 --> 04:16.249
WOULD BE FAR BETTER SPENT
SEARCHING FOR THE ANIMAL

04:16.249 --> 04:17.784
WHO ACTUALLY DID THIS THING ‐‐

04:17.784 --> 04:20.086
WHO SO CARELESSLY HIT
THIS POOR LITTLE GIRL.

04:20.086 --> 04:22.989
AND BRING THAT ANIMAL TO
JUSTICE, AND LEAVE MY SON ALONE.

04:26.760 --> 04:28.461
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

04:34.568 --> 04:36.302
HELLO?

04:36.302 --> 04:38.638
WHO IS THIS?

04:38.638 --> 04:40.140
HELLO?

04:40.140 --> 04:43.009
"TURN ON THE TV"?
WHO IS THIS?

04:56.557 --> 04:59.526
<i>THE LAST THING I WANT</i>
<i>TO SAY IS THIS ‐‐</i>

04:59.526 --> 05:03.403
<i>TO ALL OF THE PEOPLE WHO HAVE</i>
<i>RUSHED TO JUDGEMENT ON THIS,</i>

05:03.403 --> 05:05.005
<i>I GET IT, I UNDERSTAND,</i>

05:05.005 --> 05:06.507
<i>I AM WITH YOU ON THIS.</i>

05:06.507 --> 05:09.475
<i>I WOULD WANT THE HEAD</i>
<i>OF THIS PERSON, TOO.</i>

05:09.475 --> 05:10.511
<i>BUT MY SON,</i>

05:10.511 --> 05:15.849
WYATT CRYER, DID NOT DO THIS.

05:15.849 --> 05:19.019
THERE IS THE CAR.
HERE IS THE VICTIM.

05:19.019 --> 05:20.987
ARE THERE ANY QUESTIONS?

05:20.987 --> 05:23.590
<i>Woman: MY QUESTION</i>
<i>IS FOR MR. QUESTAL.</i>

05:23.590 --> 05:26.259
<i>WHY DIDN'T YOU REPORT THIS</i>
<i>TO THE POLICE?</i>

05:26.259 --> 05:28.595
<i>I WASN'T HURT THAT BAD,</i>

05:28.595 --> 05:32.533
<i>AND THE YOUNG MAN</i>
<i>WAS SINCERELY SORRY.</i>

05:32.533 --> 05:34.835
<i>Woman: JUDGE CRYER, ARE YOU</i>
<i>GOING TO BRING CHARGES</i>

05:34.835 --> 05:36.870
<i>AGAINST THIS D. A.</i>
<i>FOR WRONGFUL PROSECUTION?</i>

05:36.870 --> 05:38.839
LET'S FACE IT,
MY SON IS GUILTY,

05:38.839 --> 05:40.907
BUT HE'S NOT GUILTY
OF THIS CRIME.

05:40.907 --> 05:43.076
I'M HOPING THAT THE GREAT CITY
THAT WE LIVE IN

05:43.076 --> 05:45.145
WILL DO THE RIGHT THING
AND LET MY SON GO.

05:45.145 --> 05:47.914
Woman: DO YOU THINK THIS WILL
HURT YOUR CHANCES FOR GOVERNOR?

05:47.914 --> 05:49.816
I CAN'T THINK ABOUT
THAT RIGHT NOW.

05:49.816 --> 05:51.952
WHAT I HAVE TO THINK
ABOUT IS MY FAMILY.

05:51.952 --> 05:53.754
NOW, AS MUCH
AS I LOVE THIS STATE

05:53.754 --> 05:56.089
AND AS MUCH AS I THINK
I'D BE A GREAT ASSET TO IT,

05:56.089 --> 05:58.258
I NEED TO FOCUS ON MY SON
AND ALL THE HARD WORK

05:58.258 --> 05:59.793
THAT HE AND I HAVE
AHEAD OF US.

05:59.793 --> 06:02.202
Woman: MR. QUESTAL,
WILL YOU PRESS CHARGES?

06:02.202 --> 06:03.203
UH, NO, I WON'T.

06:03.203 --> 06:04.337
WOW.

06:04.337 --> 06:06.573
YOU ARE DEALING
WITH A MASTER.

06:06.573 --> 06:08.208
I SEE THAT.

06:08.208 --> 06:10.310
Woman: JUDGE, WHY DOES YOUR SON
LOOK SO MUCH

06:10.310 --> 06:12.679
LIKE THE SKETCH OF THE DRIVER
THAT HIT LITTLE LIZ?

06:12.679 --> 06:14.047
THAT'S AN EXCELLENT QUESTION,

06:14.047 --> 06:16.149
BUT I'M NOT ACTUALLY SURE
THAT THE COMPOSITE IS CORRECT.

06:16.149 --> 06:17.518
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,

06:17.518 --> 06:19.986
THE PERSON THAT GAVE IT
WAS ALSO UNDER THE INFLUENCE.

06:19.986 --> 06:21.154
Man: DO YOU THINK THAT

06:21.154 --> 06:22.623
YOU HAVE BEEN TREATED UNFAIRLY

06:22.623 --> 06:24.490
BECAUSE YOU'RE RUNNING
FOR GOVERNOR?

06:24.490 --> 06:27.961
UM, I HOPE THAT THAT'S
NOT THE CASE.

06:27.961 --> 06:30.764
Woman: HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT
THE D. A. ARRESTING YOUR SON?

06:30.764 --> 06:33.066
I'M JUST RELIEVED
THAT THE TRUTH IS OUT

06:33.066 --> 06:35.669
AND THAT NOW MY SON
AND I HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY

06:35.669 --> 06:37.103
TO TAKE THIS AS IT COMES.

06:37.103 --> 06:39.706
GET A POLL GOING, I WANT TO SEE
WHAT PUBLIC SENTIMENT IS.

06:39.706 --> 06:41.074
I'M ON IT.

06:41.074 --> 06:43.944
WAIT. FIRST TAKE HIM DOWN
BEFORE HE GETS TOO OFF TRACK.

06:43.944 --> 06:45.679
HE'S BEEN BRILLIANT SO FAR.

06:45.679 --> 06:47.247
ALL RIGHT.

06:47.247 --> 06:48.782
THIS IS MY SON
WYATT CRYER'S CAR.

06:48.782 --> 06:49.950
YOU CAN CHECK
THE VIN NUMBER.

06:49.950 --> 06:51.051
YOU CAN CHECK

06:51.051 --> 06:52.485
WITH THE DEPARTMENT
OF MOTOR VEHICLES.

06:52.485 --> 06:56.289
I PROMISE YOU
IT WILL ALL CHECK OUT.

06:56.289 --> 06:59.059
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
NO MORE QUESTIONS, PLEASE.

06:59.059 --> 07:02.335
I'M SURE YOU CAN UNDERSTAND
THIS HAS BEEN A TRYING ORDEAL.

07:02.335 --> 07:05.639
WE WILL BE FIELDING QUESTIONS AS
WE GO ON, BUT NOT TODAY.

07:05.639 --> 07:06.840
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

07:06.840 --> 07:08.975
DID YOU KNOW ABOUT THIS?

07:08.975 --> 07:11.311
I KNEW JIM WOULD HANDLE IT.

07:11.311 --> 07:12.445
THAT HE DID.

07:17.884 --> 07:20.521
IF ONE OF MY CHILDREN
BEHAVED THAT WAY,

07:20.521 --> 07:22.388
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD DO.

07:22.388 --> 07:23.790
ESPECIALLY MY SON.

07:26.727 --> 07:28.028
GET OUT OF HERE.

07:29.262 --> 07:31.565
YES, MA'AM.

07:37.971 --> 07:39.973
JIM CRYER.

07:41.642 --> 07:44.077
YOU'RE A CLEVER BASTARD.

07:52.986 --> 07:54.354
[ TURNS OFF TV ]

07:54.354 --> 07:55.722
[ SIGHS ]

07:55.789 --> 07:58.825
LORD HAVE MERCY, JESUS.

08:00.967 --> 08:02.603
LYING!

08:05.405 --> 08:07.541
I DON'T BUY IT.

08:11.612 --> 08:12.846
WHO ‐‐

08:13.714 --> 08:15.849
NOW, WHO ARE YOU?

08:23.790 --> 08:25.826
[ SIGHS ]

08:35.602 --> 08:37.704
WHAT'S UP, MAMA?

08:39.673 --> 08:42.042
QUINCY?

08:42.042 --> 08:43.744
YEAH.

08:45.746 --> 08:47.447
HOW'D YOU GET IN HERE?

08:47.447 --> 08:49.583
YOU ONLY HAVE BARS
ON THE FRONT DOOR.

08:49.583 --> 08:51.652
YOU KNOW THAT'S
REAL STUPID, RIGHT?

08:51.652 --> 08:53.887
GET OUT.

08:53.887 --> 08:56.056
WHERE'S CANDY?

08:56.056 --> 08:58.091
I DON'T KNOW.

08:58.091 --> 08:59.392
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR HER.

08:59.392 --> 09:01.234
GET OUT OF HERE!

09:01.234 --> 09:03.904
WHAT, SHE DON'T LIVE HERE?

09:03.904 --> 09:07.307
YOU KNOW GOOD AND WELL
I DON'T DEAL WITH MY DAUGHTER.

09:07.307 --> 09:08.909
NOW, YOU GET OUT OF HERE.

09:23.123 --> 09:25.325
NOW, YOU GET OUT
OF MY HOUSE, QUINCY,

09:25.325 --> 09:27.260
OR I'M GOING TO CALL
THE POLICE.

09:27.260 --> 09:29.129
GO AHEAD.

09:29.129 --> 09:30.697
OKAY.

09:30.697 --> 09:32.465
FINE.

09:37.538 --> 09:39.039
HELLO?

09:39.039 --> 09:40.607
YES, THERE'S SOMEONE
IN MY HOUSE,

09:40.607 --> 09:41.608
AND HE WON'T LEAVE.

09:41.608 --> 09:44.477
HE BROKE IN.

09:45.679 --> 09:48.982
YES. HIS NAME
IS QUINCY MAXWELL.

09:48.982 --> 09:51.017
OKAY.

09:51.017 --> 09:53.620
YES, MA'AM.
I'LL STAY ON THE PHONE.

09:53.620 --> 09:56.489
THEY'RE COMING, QUINCY.

09:56.489 --> 09:57.624
OKAY.

09:57.624 --> 09:59.693
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

09:59.693 --> 10:01.134
WHERE'S CANDY?
I DON'T KNOW!

10:01.134 --> 10:02.435
IF YOU WANT TO FIND HER,

10:02.435 --> 10:04.971
YOU GO ON OUT THERE
SOMEWHERE AND LOOK FOR HER.

10:04.971 --> 10:06.472
SHE GAVE ME UP.

10:06.472 --> 10:07.608
I DON'T CARE!

10:07.608 --> 10:08.975
DO YOU NOT UNDERSTAND ME?

10:08.975 --> 10:11.678
I DON'T DEAL WITH HER AND I'M
NOT ABOUT TO DEAL WITH YOU.

10:11.678 --> 10:13.279
NOW, GET OUT OF MY HOUSE, BOY.

10:13.279 --> 10:14.648
SHE GAVE ME UP.

10:14.648 --> 10:17.117
NO, MA'AM,
HE'S NOT LEAVING.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.287
THEY'RE COMING?

10:21.287 --> 10:22.455
THANK YOU.

10:22.455 --> 10:26.860
HAD ME ON LOCKDOWN
FOR THREE YEARS.

10:26.860 --> 10:29.863
YOU TELL HER I'M OUT NOW.

10:29.863 --> 10:33.166
AND I WILL FIND HER.

10:33.166 --> 10:35.135
YOU'VE BEEN IN JAIL?

10:35.135 --> 10:36.837
HELL YEAH.

10:36.837 --> 10:39.506
WHERE'S
MY GRANDBABY, QUINCY?

10:39.506 --> 10:41.441
WHAT?

10:41.441 --> 10:43.209
WHERE IS MY GRANDBABY?

10:43.209 --> 10:45.512
SHE SAID YOU HAD HIM.
NOW, WHERE IS HE?

10:45.512 --> 10:47.681
SHE SAID I HAD HIM?

10:47.681 --> 10:49.482
YES.

10:49.482 --> 10:54.220
HOW THE HELL AM I SUPPOSED
TO HAVE HIM IN JAIL?

10:54.220 --> 10:56.422
WHERE IS HE, QUINCY?!

10:56.422 --> 10:58.525
EXCUSE ME.
WHAT?

10:58.525 --> 11:00.967
YEAH, I KNOW HIM.

11:00.967 --> 11:02.736
NO, HE'S NOT WELCOME HERE!

11:02.736 --> 11:05.038
WHERE IS MY GRANDBABY?!
WHERE ‐‐

11:05.038 --> 11:06.472
[ SCREAMS ]

11:16.116 --> 11:18.184
[ DOG BARKING ]

11:24.791 --> 11:26.459
HELLO?

11:27.828 --> 11:29.830
YES, HE JUST LEFT.

11:31.665 --> 11:32.999
OKAY.

11:32.999 --> 11:35.602
NO, THANK YOU.

11:35.602 --> 11:38.705
OKAY. OKAY.

11:38.705 --> 11:40.440
YES.

11:40.974 --> 11:44.110
I'LL LOCK THE DOORS.

11:44.110 --> 11:46.780
AND I'LL CLOSE
ALL THE WINDOWS, YES.

11:48.381 --> 11:50.350
THANK YOU.

11:50.350 --> 11:51.685
OKAY.

12:02.002 --> 12:04.004
WELL DONE.
I JUST HOPE IT WORKS.

12:04.004 --> 12:05.071
IT WILL.

12:07.107 --> 12:08.509
JIM?

12:08.509 --> 12:10.343
Jim:
WOW, ARE YOU STILL HERE?

12:10.343 --> 12:13.113
YEAH, WELL, MAGGIE
AND I HAD A LITTLE TALK.

12:13.113 --> 12:14.347
REALLY?
YEAH.

12:14.347 --> 12:17.050
SO, SHE'S STILL WORKING
ON THE CAMPAIGN? HUH.

12:17.050 --> 12:18.552
WE ARE JUST PULLING
THE DATA NOW,

12:18.552 --> 12:21.054
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE YOU TURNED
THIS TOWN QUICKLY IN YOUR FAVOR.

12:21.054 --> 12:22.422
IMAGINE THAT.

12:22.422 --> 12:24.224
PERSONAL STORIES ABOUT
YOUR SON WERE A NICE TOUCH.

12:24.224 --> 12:25.391
YOU CAME ACROSS VERY HUMAN.

12:25.391 --> 12:26.793
WE COULDN'T HAVE
COACHED YOU BETTER.

12:26.793 --> 12:28.128
NO, ACTUALLY, I COULD'VE.

12:28.128 --> 12:30.964
IT'S EASY TO TALK ABOUT
MY CHILDREN WITH AFFECTION.

12:30.964 --> 12:32.999
I LOVE THEM VERY MUCH.
YES, THAT WAS OBVIOUS.

12:32.999 --> 12:35.569
BUT THAT PART ABOUT YOUR WIFE ‐‐
NOT SO MUCH TRUTH IN THAT.

12:35.569 --> 12:37.871
GOT ME THERE.
THANKS, MAGGIE.

12:37.871 --> 12:40.040
JUST DON'T LET IT HAPPEN
AGAIN, JIM.

12:40.040 --> 12:42.743
David: JIM WAS LOOKING OUT
FOR HIS SON.

12:42.743 --> 12:44.545
SURE YOU CAN
APPRECIATE THAT.

12:44.545 --> 12:45.646
YES, I CAN.

12:45.646 --> 12:47.113
I THINK IT'S GREAT
WHEN A MAN

12:47.113 --> 12:48.782
CAN GO ALL OUT
TO PROTECT HIS SON.

12:48.782 --> 12:50.884
ARE YOU THAT KIND OF FATHER,
MR. HARRINGTON?

12:53.253 --> 12:54.588
EXCUSE ME?

12:54.588 --> 12:56.222
JEFFERY ‐‐

12:56.222 --> 12:58.625
WOULD YOU GO ALL OUT
TO PROTECT HIM?

12:58.625 --> 13:01.467
YES, I WOULD.

13:01.467 --> 13:03.737
AND YOUR WIFE?

13:04.938 --> 13:06.740
YES.

13:06.740 --> 13:08.742
SHE WOULD.

13:08.742 --> 13:10.310
GOOD.

13:10.310 --> 13:13.413
YES, IT IS.

13:13.413 --> 13:14.681
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

13:14.681 --> 13:16.583
I'LL GET IT.

13:16.583 --> 13:17.918
THANK YOU.

13:17.918 --> 13:19.452
CAN YOU GET ON THE RESEARCH?

13:19.452 --> 13:20.721
RIGHT AWAY.
THANKS.

13:25.491 --> 13:29.095
D.A.'S OFFICE.
THEY WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

13:29.095 --> 13:30.363
OH.

13:30.363 --> 13:31.565
JUDGE JIM CRYER.

13:31.565 --> 13:33.800
BEFORE YOU SAY A WORD,
I WANT TO LET YOU KNOW

13:33.800 --> 13:35.902
I'M NOT HAVING
ANY KIND OF DISCUSSION

13:35.902 --> 13:38.271
UNLESS YOU AGREE
TO RELEASE MY SON.

13:40.707 --> 13:42.743
I'M ON MY WAY.

13:44.044 --> 13:46.146
WHAT WAS THAT?

13:46.146 --> 13:49.315
D.A. WOULD LIKE TO DISCUSS
A DEAL.

13:49.315 --> 13:50.483
EXCELLENT.

13:50.483 --> 13:52.252
YES, IT IS.

13:54.187 --> 13:55.822
THAT ALL WORKED OUT.

13:55.822 --> 13:57.290
YES, IT DID.

13:57.290 --> 13:58.391
IS IT TRUE?

13:58.391 --> 13:59.826
WHAT?

13:59.826 --> 14:01.902
DID WYATT REALLY HIT
THAT STRANGER?

14:01.902 --> 14:03.837
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

14:03.837 --> 14:05.438
COME ON, DAVID.
IS IT TRUE?

14:05.438 --> 14:08.308
I MEAN, IT'S ALL A LITTLE
COINCIDENTAL, DON'T YOU THINK?

14:08.308 --> 14:11.845
I THINK YOU'VE BEEN WATCHING
TOO MANY CRIME SHOWS.

14:11.845 --> 14:13.146
I DON'T WATCH CRIME SHOWS.

14:13.146 --> 14:14.881
SOMETHING HAS YOU THINKING
THIS WAY.

14:14.881 --> 14:16.583
I JUST PAY ATTENTION.

14:16.583 --> 14:17.718
YOU KNOW, LIKE I'M...

14:17.718 --> 14:21.622
PAYING ATTENTION TO THE LINT
THAT'S ON YOUR SUIT.

14:21.622 --> 14:22.856
REALLY?

14:22.856 --> 14:26.593
LOW THREAD COUNT.
HOTEL SHEETS.

14:26.593 --> 14:28.695
EXCUSE ME?

14:28.695 --> 14:30.697
YOUR WIFE WOULDN'T
BE CAUGHT DEAD

14:30.697 --> 14:32.733
WITH SHEETS LIKE THAT
ON HER BED.

14:32.733 --> 14:33.834
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

14:37.103 --> 14:39.205
EVERYTHING'S FINE.
THANK YOU.

14:41.107 --> 14:42.876
OKAY.

14:48.381 --> 14:50.984
THERE'S ‐‐ THERE'S NO LINT
ON MY SUIT.

14:52.819 --> 14:56.256
I SAW YOU CHECKING INTO
THE SARANDON HOTEL.

14:56.256 --> 14:58.124
WE'RE ALL STAYING THERE.

14:58.124 --> 14:59.760
ARE YOU?

14:59.760 --> 15:01.001
YEAH.

15:02.736 --> 15:03.970
OKAY.

15:03.970 --> 15:07.541
SO, YOU WANT TO COME CLEAN?

15:07.541 --> 15:10.644
UH...

15:10.644 --> 15:13.547
NOTHING TO COME CLEAN ABOUT.

15:13.547 --> 15:15.916
OKAY.

15:15.916 --> 15:19.586
WELL, I'M ALWAYS AN EAR
TO BEND IF YOU NEED IT.

15:19.586 --> 15:20.987
WELL, I'LL...

15:20.987 --> 15:24.490
KEEP THAT IN MIND.

15:24.490 --> 15:27.060
YOU DO THAT.

15:29.495 --> 15:32.198
UM...

15:32.198 --> 15:33.600
EXCUSE ME.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.035
MM‐HMM. SURE.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.418
IS THIS GOING TO TAKE
A LONG TIME?

15:52.418 --> 15:54.187
WELL, WE ARE
CALLING IT IN RIGHT NOW.

15:54.187 --> 15:56.422
SO, IN ABOUT FIVE MINUTES
AN APB WILL BE PUT OUT.

15:56.422 --> 15:58.925
OKAY, 'CAUSE I HAVE TO GET BACK
TO THE HOSPITAL TO MY SON.

15:58.925 --> 16:00.193
OKAY, WELL,
WE HAVE THE REPORT.

16:00.193 --> 16:01.334
WHICH WAY DID HE GO?

16:01.334 --> 16:02.536
HE WENT THAT WAY SOMEWHERE.

16:02.536 --> 16:04.437
OKAY, YOU WILL
PRESS CHARGES?

16:04.437 --> 16:05.438
YES, I WILL.

16:05.438 --> 16:07.407
SMART WOMAN.
WE'LL FIND HIM.

16:07.407 --> 16:09.109
THANK YOU.

16:09.109 --> 16:10.210
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

16:10.210 --> 16:11.612
THANK YOU, OFFICERS.

16:13.814 --> 16:15.015
HANNA, WHAT'S GOING ON?

16:15.015 --> 16:16.683
HEY. WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

16:16.683 --> 16:17.951
I HEARD IT ON THE RADIO.

16:17.951 --> 16:20.220
OH. MY DAUGHTER'S
THUGGISH‐ASS BOYFRIEND.

16:20.220 --> 16:21.922
YOU ALL RIGHT?

16:21.922 --> 16:22.989
YEAH.

16:22.989 --> 16:23.990
WHAT'D HE DO?

16:23.990 --> 16:25.058
HE WAS IN MY HOUSE.

16:25.058 --> 16:26.292
YOU LET HIM IN?
NO.

16:26.292 --> 16:28.461
WELL, WHAT'D HE SAY?
WHAT'D HE WANT?

16:28.461 --> 16:29.830
HE WAS LOOKING
FOR MY DAUGHTER.

16:29.830 --> 16:32.332
OH. OKAY.

16:32.332 --> 16:34.067
SURE YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

16:34.067 --> 16:36.737
YEAH.
THANK YOU FOR COMING.

16:36.737 --> 16:39.172
OH, COME ON,
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

16:39.172 --> 16:40.541
HOW'D HE GET IN?

16:40.541 --> 16:42.609
THROUGH THE WINDOW.

16:42.609 --> 16:43.677
HANNA.

16:43.677 --> 16:45.712
YOU NEED TO PUT BARS ON.

16:45.712 --> 16:49.349
I KNOW. BUT EVERYBODY IN
THE NEIGHBORHOOD KNOWS ME.

16:49.349 --> 16:52.052
YEAH, THAT'S NOT ALWAYS
A GOOD THING.

16:53.787 --> 16:55.355
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

16:55.355 --> 16:56.857
I WAS REALLY GOOD.

16:56.857 --> 16:58.191
'TIL THIS GUY.

16:58.191 --> 16:59.359
YEAH.

17:00.861 --> 17:04.170
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN
GOING THROUGH A LOT.

17:04.170 --> 17:06.540
THE DEATH
OF YOUR SON AND ALL.

17:06.540 --> 17:10.677
NO. BYRON, MY BABY,
IS ALIVE.

17:12.679 --> 17:15.115
OH. HANNA.

17:15.115 --> 17:16.883
NO, NO, NO, NO.

17:16.883 --> 17:18.885
NO, I'M NOT CRAZY.

17:18.885 --> 17:20.587
I'M NOT SEEING SPIRITS.

17:20.587 --> 17:24.390
HE WAS MOVED TO ANOTHER HOSPITAL
AND I DIDN'T KNOW IT.

17:24.390 --> 17:26.126
WHAT?
YES.

17:26.126 --> 17:27.894
MY EX‐BOSS MOVED HIM.

17:27.894 --> 17:29.029
OH.

17:29.029 --> 17:30.030
WOW!

17:30.030 --> 17:31.131
YEAH!

17:31.131 --> 17:32.966
OH, HANNA.
THAT'S GREAT!

17:32.966 --> 17:37.504
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH, IT IS.

17:46.547 --> 17:47.814
I, UM...

17:49.916 --> 17:51.985
UH, YEAH.

17:53.720 --> 17:55.756
I HAVE TO GET BACK TO HIM.

17:55.756 --> 17:58.559
OKAY.

17:58.559 --> 18:01.234
I'LL GIVE YOU A RIDE.

18:01.234 --> 18:03.069
YEAH.

18:03.069 --> 18:05.405
AND I'LL TAKE YOU UP
ON THAT RIDE.

18:05.405 --> 18:08.441
HE'S AT MERCY.

18:08.441 --> 18:11.512
LET ME JUST GET MY PURSE
AND LOCK THE DOOR.

18:11.512 --> 18:12.846
OKAY.

18:12.846 --> 18:13.914
[ LAUGHS ]

18:13.914 --> 18:15.148
COME ON NOW.

18:15.148 --> 18:16.717
ALL RIGHT.

18:43.744 --> 18:45.712
THIS IS VERY EMBARRASSING
FOR THE D. A.

18:45.712 --> 18:47.848
JUDGE CRYER'S SON
HAS AN ADDICTION PROBLEM,

18:47.848 --> 18:50.684
AND HE'S BEEN VERY ADAMANT
ABOUT GETTING HIS SON TREATMENT.

18:50.684 --> 18:52.586
THE D. A. RUSHED TO GET
A CONVICTION,

18:52.586 --> 18:54.721
AND NOW THE GRANDFATHER
OF THE LITTLE GIRL

18:54.721 --> 18:56.056
IS DEMANDING ANSWERS.

18:56.056 --> 18:58.324
WE HAVE NO OFFICIAL COMMENT
FROM THE D. A.'S OFFICE,

18:58.324 --> 19:01.067
BUT I AM SURE THAT HEADS
ARE ROLLING IN THERE RIGHT NOW.

19:01.067 --> 19:03.704
GET IN THE CAR, WYATT.

19:03.704 --> 19:05.706
WYATT, HOW ARE YOU?
EXCUSE ME.

19:05.706 --> 19:07.541
MY SON HAS BEEN THROUGH A LOT.

19:07.541 --> 19:09.743
WE'RE REQUESTING PRIVACY NOW,
PLEASE?

19:12.245 --> 19:14.581
AND THERE YOU HAVE IT.

19:14.581 --> 19:18.218
A VERY EMOTIONAL AND I'M SURE
RELIEVED FATHER AND SON,

19:18.218 --> 19:21.522
HEADING HOME AFTER
AN EXTRAORDINARILY TRYING TIME

19:21.522 --> 19:23.023
FOR THE CRYER FAMILY.

19:23.023 --> 19:26.760
REPORTING LIVE OUTSIDE POLICE
HEADQUARTERS FOR 17 NEWS.

19:56.523 --> 19:58.892
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN HERE?

20:01.968 --> 20:04.571
I ‐‐ I WAS LOOKING
FOR CANDACE.

20:04.571 --> 20:06.707
SHE'S NOT HERE.

20:07.908 --> 20:09.209
WHERE IS SHE?

20:09.209 --> 20:11.411
I DON'T KNOW.

20:11.411 --> 20:14.447
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH THAT GUN?

20:14.447 --> 20:17.584
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH KEYS?

20:17.584 --> 20:21.454
UM, I ‐‐ I ALREADY
HAD THEM.

20:21.454 --> 20:22.723
GIVE THEM TO ME.

20:22.723 --> 20:24.490
OKAY, OKAY.

20:26.527 --> 20:28.094
THANKS.

20:30.864 --> 20:33.433
ARE YOU GOING
TO ANSWER MY QUESTION?

20:33.433 --> 20:35.769
MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS, JEFFERY.

20:35.769 --> 20:40.473
UH...AMANDA.
THAT ‐‐ THAT ‐‐

20:40.473 --> 20:41.775
WHAT?

20:41.775 --> 20:42.776
THAT'S ‐‐ THAT'S SERIOUS.

20:42.776 --> 20:43.777
I'LL SAY.

20:43.777 --> 20:45.679
WANT TO SEE HOW IT WORKS?

20:45.679 --> 20:47.313
NO. NO, NO.
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

20:47.313 --> 20:48.782
THEN GET OUT OF HERE.

20:48.782 --> 20:50.250
OKAY, OKAY.

20:50.250 --> 20:51.685
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?!

20:51.685 --> 20:53.353
TELL ME WHY YOU'RE HERE.

20:53.353 --> 20:55.722
WHY?!

20:57.490 --> 21:00.060
AMANDA, I CAME TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT YOUR BROTHER.

21:00.060 --> 21:02.335
DO YOU EVEN KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON WITH HIM?

21:02.335 --> 21:03.604
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

21:03.604 --> 21:07.541
GIVE ME THE GUN AND I'LL ‐‐
I'LL TELL YOU.

21:07.541 --> 21:09.510
I'M NOT GIVING YOU MY GUN.

21:09.510 --> 21:10.511
YOUR GUN?

21:10.511 --> 21:12.245
YEAH, I BOUGHT IT.

21:13.479 --> 21:15.415
IT'S MINE.

21:18.418 --> 21:21.487
OKAY, WELL THEN, I GUESS
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU ABOUT IT.

21:21.487 --> 21:22.789
YOU'D BETTER TELL ME.

21:22.789 --> 21:25.291
OKAY, WAIT, DON'T WAVE
THAT AROUND, PLEASE?

21:25.291 --> 21:26.359
JUST DON'T?

21:26.359 --> 21:27.828
IT'S NOT LOADED, JEFFERY.

21:31.632 --> 21:34.167
WOULD YOU STOP?
COULD YOU LOWER IT THEN?

21:40.206 --> 21:42.008
WHY DO YOU HAVE THAT?

21:44.845 --> 21:46.913
I TOLD YOU.

21:46.913 --> 21:48.148
STOP.

21:50.116 --> 21:53.386
PLEASE, JUST LOWER IT.
THAT'S ALL I'M ASKING.

21:53.386 --> 21:54.555
JUST LOWER IT.

21:54.555 --> 21:56.957
AMANDA, AMANDA?

21:56.957 --> 21:58.859
STOP, STOP.

21:58.859 --> 22:00.233
LOWER IT, PLEASE?

22:05.839 --> 22:07.440
ALL RIGHT, UM...

22:07.440 --> 22:11.845
YOU TOLD ME THAT YOU WANTED
TO KILL YOUR FAMILY.

22:11.845 --> 22:13.413
I AM.

22:13.413 --> 22:15.415
I'M GOING TO DO IT.

22:15.415 --> 22:18.919
AMANDA, BUT YOU ALSO SAID THAT
YOU WERE JUST KIDDING.

22:18.919 --> 22:21.855
I AM.

22:21.855 --> 22:23.790
THIS ISN'T FUNNY.

22:23.790 --> 22:26.527
LOOK...THIS GUN,

22:26.527 --> 22:30.597
IT MAKES ME FEEL POWERFUL,

22:30.597 --> 22:33.634
AND GOOD AND STRONG.

22:33.634 --> 22:35.569
CAN I HAVE IT?

22:35.569 --> 22:37.303
WHY?

22:39.139 --> 22:40.473
I WANT TO ‐‐
I WANT TO FEEL THAT.

22:40.473 --> 22:41.508
I WANT TO FEEL THAT ‐‐

22:41.508 --> 22:44.845
NO, YOU CAN'T.
YOU'RE A MAN.

22:44.845 --> 22:47.480
YOU ALREADY FEEL STRONG.

22:47.480 --> 22:50.050
YOU ABUSE AND HURT WOMEN.

22:50.050 --> 22:52.218
ARROGANT.

22:52.218 --> 22:56.790
OKAY, I ‐‐ I GUESS I CAN'T
TALK TO YOU ABOUT WYATT.

22:56.790 --> 23:00.567
FINE. I'LL PUT IT AWAY.

23:05.338 --> 23:07.974
I'LL PUT IT AWAY.

23:18.351 --> 23:20.153
IS THAT BETTER,
YOU LITTLE BITCH?

23:20.153 --> 23:22.923
OKAY, ENOUGH
WITH THE NAME CALLING.

23:22.923 --> 23:24.591
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

23:24.591 --> 23:26.426
WHERE'S ‐‐ WHERE'S CANDACE?

23:26.426 --> 23:28.695
SHE HASN'T BEEN HERE
ALL DAY.

23:28.695 --> 23:30.330
SHE HASN'T?

23:30.330 --> 23:32.465
NO.

23:32.465 --> 23:35.468
AND IT'S BEEN ALL DAY?

23:35.468 --> 23:37.270
YES.

23:37.270 --> 23:39.139
DID SHE TELL YOU
WHERE SHE WAS GOING?

23:39.139 --> 23:41.141
NO.

23:41.141 --> 23:46.547
OKAY, WELL, I THINK MAYBE YOU
SHOULD TRY GIVING HER A CALL.

23:46.547 --> 23:48.448
I HAVE BEEN.

23:48.448 --> 23:50.851
OKAY, SO HAVE I.

23:50.851 --> 23:53.987
WELL, OBVIOUSLY, SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO BE BOTHERED RIGHT NOW.

23:53.987 --> 23:57.824
HAS SHE EVER DONE ANYTHING
LIKE THIS BEFORE?

23:57.824 --> 23:59.626
HUH‐UH.

23:59.626 --> 24:00.834
NO.

24:00.834 --> 24:03.670
HMM.
IT'S ODD.

24:03.670 --> 24:07.373
IT IS.
TELL ME ABOUT WYATT.

24:07.373 --> 24:08.809
HE'S FINE.

24:08.809 --> 24:11.144
BUT HE WAS ARRESTED.

24:14.180 --> 24:15.982
WHY IS THAT FUNNY?

24:15.982 --> 24:17.618
WHAT DID HE DO NOW?

24:17.618 --> 24:19.720
HE'S SUCH A PROBLEM CHILD.

24:21.588 --> 24:22.923
AMANDA ‐‐

24:22.923 --> 24:25.592
WHAT? A D. U. I.?

24:25.592 --> 24:26.893
[ LAUGHS ]

24:26.893 --> 24:27.894
HIT AND RUN.

24:27.894 --> 24:31.532
THAT IS SO LIKE HIM.

24:33.066 --> 24:35.401
AMANDA, THIS ISN'T FUNNY.

24:35.401 --> 24:38.204
YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH HIM.

24:39.973 --> 24:42.042
OKAY, GOD, AMANDA.

24:42.042 --> 24:44.410
NO, I THINK YOU ARE.

24:44.410 --> 24:47.648
CANDACE WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

24:47.648 --> 24:50.416
YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH WYATT.

24:53.119 --> 24:54.721
YOU WANT TO KNOW WHAT
I THINK?

24:54.721 --> 24:56.823
I THINK THAT YOU NEED
TO COME WITH ME

24:56.823 --> 24:58.559
AND LET ME GET YOU
SOME HELP.

24:58.559 --> 25:02.569
AND I THINK YOU NEED TO THINK
ABOUT GETTING OUT OF HERE.

25:02.569 --> 25:04.204
AMANDA, I THINK ‐‐

25:04.204 --> 25:06.206
"AMANDA, I THINK..."

25:07.608 --> 25:08.809
YOU NEED...

25:08.809 --> 25:09.943
"YOU NEED..."

25:09.943 --> 25:11.311
OKAY.

25:11.311 --> 25:12.312
"OKAY."

25:12.312 --> 25:13.880
WOULD YOU STOP?
"WOULD YOU STOP?"

25:13.880 --> 25:16.149
NO.
"NO."

25:16.149 --> 25:18.051
Both: I THINK.
AMANDA.

25:18.051 --> 25:19.119
"AMANDA."

25:19.119 --> 25:21.655
Both: AMANDA, AMANDA...

25:21.655 --> 25:23.990
AMANDA, AMANDA!

25:23.990 --> 25:27.661
JEFFERY, YOU NEED
TO GET OUT OF HERE.

25:27.661 --> 25:30.163
OR I'M GOING TO GET
MY GUN.

25:30.163 --> 25:33.133
I'M GOING TO GET MY GUN,
MY GUN, MY GUN...

25:33.133 --> 25:36.069
my gun, my gun, my gun,
my gun, my gun...

25:36.069 --> 25:37.470
OKAY.

25:37.470 --> 25:39.506
"OKAY."

25:39.506 --> 25:40.507
NOW!

25:40.507 --> 25:42.108
ALL RIGHT.

26:02.603 --> 26:05.371
JUST GOT OUT OF JAIL.

26:05.371 --> 26:06.840
FOR WHAT?

26:06.840 --> 26:09.442
HE WAS IN FOR MURDER.

26:11.011 --> 26:13.013
GOT RELEASED YESTERDAY.

26:13.013 --> 26:16.883
MAN, THIS DUDE IS TROUBLE.

26:16.883 --> 26:20.020
WHAT'S ALL THAT?

26:20.020 --> 26:22.288
RAP SHEET.

26:22.288 --> 26:25.759
[ SCOFFS ]
MY DAUGHTER.

26:25.759 --> 26:27.661
SHE SURE KNOWS HOW
TO PICK 'EM.

26:27.661 --> 26:30.030
HMPH. SHE'S TROUBLE,
TOO, HUH?

26:30.030 --> 26:32.465
MMM, YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

26:32.465 --> 26:34.701
SPEAKING OF WHICH...

26:34.701 --> 26:39.005
BYRON, I NEED YOUR HELP
WITH SOMETHING.

26:39.005 --> 26:41.274
ANYTHING.

26:42.576 --> 26:44.778
I CAN'T FIND
MY GRANDBABY.

26:46.412 --> 26:47.781
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

26:49.650 --> 26:52.485
MY DAUGHTER WON'T TELL ME
WHERE HE IS.

26:52.485 --> 26:57.791
WELL, SHE SAID HE WAS WITH
HIS FATHER, THAT FOOL,

26:57.791 --> 26:59.826
BUT HE JUST GOT OUT OF JAIL.

27:01.501 --> 27:03.436
I DON'T KNOW WHERE
MY GRANDBABY IS.

27:03.436 --> 27:04.538
ALL RIGHT.

27:04.538 --> 27:06.406
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

27:06.406 --> 27:09.643
QUINCY DELON YOUNG.

27:10.977 --> 27:12.212
HOW OLD IS HE?

27:13.514 --> 27:16.683
HE'S FIVE NOW.

27:16.683 --> 27:19.520
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL LOOK INTO IT.

27:21.522 --> 27:23.924
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

27:29.029 --> 27:31.264
I'M WORRIED
ABOUT THAT BABY.

27:31.264 --> 27:32.699
I DON'T KNOW.

27:32.699 --> 27:35.936
SOMETHING
JUST DON'T FEEL RIGHT.

27:35.936 --> 27:38.539
I HAVE A BAD FEELING ABOUT IT.

27:38.539 --> 27:40.106
SOON AS I DROP YOU OFF,

27:40.106 --> 27:42.676
I'LL HEAD OVER
TO CHILDREN'S SERVICES.

27:44.244 --> 27:46.079
THANK YOU.

27:51.852 --> 27:53.587
BOY.

27:54.821 --> 27:56.990
GOT A LOT
GOING ON THESE DAYS, GIRL.

27:56.990 --> 27:58.391
[ LAUGHS ]

27:59.926 --> 28:02.836
WHO YOU TELLING?
HMM.

28:02.836 --> 28:04.370
SEE THE NEWS?

28:05.939 --> 28:07.273
YEAH.

28:07.273 --> 28:08.609
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

28:08.609 --> 28:10.010
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

28:10.010 --> 28:12.278
THINK THAT MAN
IS COVERING UP SOMETHING.

28:12.278 --> 28:13.413
WHO?

28:13.413 --> 28:15.982
HIS FATHER.
JIM CRYER.

28:15.982 --> 28:18.151
I DON'T BELIEVE
THAT MESS FOR A SECOND.

28:18.151 --> 28:20.486
THEY HAVE THE CAR, HANNA.

28:20.486 --> 28:22.322
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

28:22.322 --> 28:26.126
I TALKED TO SOME BUDDIES
OF MINE.

28:26.126 --> 28:27.493
THEY THINK IT'S THE CAR.

28:27.493 --> 28:30.196
I'M TELLING YOU,
IF THERE'S DNA ON THAT CAR,

28:30.196 --> 28:31.364
THEY WILL FIND IT.

28:31.364 --> 28:33.266
NOT IF HE CLEANED IT.

28:33.266 --> 28:35.335
I DON'T THINK JIM'S
THAT KIND OF GUY.

28:35.335 --> 28:37.137
YOU KNOW HIM?

28:37.137 --> 28:39.506
JUDGE CRYER? NAH.

28:39.506 --> 28:40.741
NEVER MET HIM.

28:40.741 --> 28:44.010
WELL THEN, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT KIND OF GUY HE IS.

28:44.010 --> 28:46.012
NO.

28:46.012 --> 28:48.582
GUESS I DON'T.

28:48.582 --> 28:51.685
BUT I THINK WE SHOULD BE LOOKING
FOR THE PERSON WHO DID THIS.

28:51.685 --> 28:54.487
THE PERSON WHO DID THIS
IS IN JAIL RIGHT NOW.

28:54.487 --> 28:55.656
YOU REALLY FEEL THAT WAY?

28:55.656 --> 28:57.223
YES.

28:57.223 --> 28:58.258
OKAY.

28:58.258 --> 28:59.793
MM‐HMM, AND I'M GOING
TO TELL THE D. A.

28:59.793 --> 29:01.101
ARE YOU?

29:01.101 --> 29:02.636
YES, I AM.

29:02.636 --> 29:05.906
I'M NOT GOING TO LET THEM
GET AWAY WITH THIS.

29:05.906 --> 29:09.342
BUT DIDN'T HIS WIFE
JUST MOVE YOUR SON?

29:12.345 --> 29:13.780
YEAH, SHE DID.

29:17.350 --> 29:20.821
I THINK SHE'S COUNTING
ON THAT TO KEEP ME SILENT.

29:22.455 --> 29:23.957
WOW.

29:23.957 --> 29:26.660
THESE MUST BE
SOME RUTHLESS PEOPLE.

29:26.660 --> 29:29.830
WELL, HER HUSBAND
TRULY IS.

29:29.830 --> 29:33.800
TRYING TO MAKE ME THINK
I WAS CRAZY.

29:33.800 --> 29:38.605
OH, THAT MAN PISSED ME OFF.

29:38.605 --> 29:41.074
THEY NOT GOING
TO GET AWAY WITH THIS.

29:41.074 --> 29:42.142
OH, NOT AT ALL.

30:03.336 --> 30:05.506
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

30:14.147 --> 30:15.181
HI, CELINE.

30:15.181 --> 30:16.249
HI, JEFFERY.

30:16.249 --> 30:18.018
IS MR. AND MRS. CRYER HERE?

30:18.018 --> 30:20.521
MR. CRYER'S NOT HERE.
BUT MRS. CRYER IS.

30:20.521 --> 30:21.588
SHE'S ON THE LANAI.

30:21.588 --> 30:22.856
OKAY. THANKS.

30:22.856 --> 30:24.257
YOU'RE WELCOME.

30:31.164 --> 30:32.599
CRYER.

30:32.599 --> 30:35.268
JEFFERY.

30:36.603 --> 30:37.704
HI.

30:37.704 --> 30:38.739
HI.

30:39.806 --> 30:41.908
HOW ARE YOU?

30:41.908 --> 30:43.276
FINE.

30:43.276 --> 30:45.278
HOW ARE YOU DOING?
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME TEA?

30:45.278 --> 30:47.113
OH, NO.
NO, THANKS.

30:47.113 --> 30:48.248
WELL,

30:48.248 --> 30:51.484
I'M MUCH BETTER NOW THAT
WYATT'S ON HIS WAY HOME.

30:51.484 --> 30:52.619
IS HE?
YES.

30:52.619 --> 30:55.188
I SAW THE PRESS CONFERENCE.

30:55.188 --> 30:57.691
SO DID I.

30:59.259 --> 31:00.767
SO, IT WORKED.

31:00.767 --> 31:03.103
WHAT WORKED?

31:03.103 --> 31:04.938
THE STORY.

31:07.407 --> 31:09.375
THAT IS THE TRUTH, JEFFERY.

31:11.011 --> 31:13.614
YEAH. THE TRUTH.

31:13.614 --> 31:17.483
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

31:17.483 --> 31:20.286
I SAW AMANDA TODAY.

31:20.286 --> 31:22.623
AND?

31:22.623 --> 31:24.558
SHE BOUGHT A GUN.

31:26.693 --> 31:27.761
WHAT?

31:27.761 --> 31:29.262
YEAH, SHE DID.

31:29.262 --> 31:30.931
HOW CAN THEY SELL
HER A GUN?

31:30.931 --> 31:33.466
DON'T THEY KNOW THAT
SHE IS MENTALLY ILL?

31:33.466 --> 31:35.636
NO, MRS. CRYER, THEY DON'T
CARE ABOUT THAT.

31:35.636 --> 31:37.203
ALL THEY WANT IS THE MONEY.

31:37.203 --> 31:38.572
WELL, WHAT DID SHE SAY?

31:38.572 --> 31:39.973
THE SAME.

31:39.973 --> 31:42.175
THAT SHE'S JUST GOING
TO KILL ALL OF US.

31:42.175 --> 31:44.210
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT SHE SAID.

31:44.210 --> 31:45.478
OH, THAT GIRL.

31:45.478 --> 31:48.081
I REALLY THINK THAT YOU SHOULD
HAVE HER COMMITTED.

31:48.081 --> 31:50.416
SHE'S NOT ONLY A DANGER
TO HERSELF, BUT ALSO TO OTHERS.

31:52.753 --> 31:54.555
ALL RIGHT.

31:54.555 --> 31:55.622
THANK YOU.

31:55.622 --> 31:59.125
I'LL TALK TO MR. CRYER
WHEN HE GETS HOME.

31:59.125 --> 32:00.601
OKAY.

32:00.601 --> 32:03.203
I'M SORRY.

32:03.203 --> 32:04.771
IT'S FINE, JEFFERY.

32:04.771 --> 32:05.972
IT'S FINE.

32:05.972 --> 32:08.709
CAN I ‐‐ CAN I WAIT
FOR WYATT?

32:08.709 --> 32:10.911
I DON'T THINK THAT'S
A VERY GOOD IDEA.

32:10.911 --> 32:13.313
HE'S NOT IN THE BEST
HEAD SPACE RIGHT NOW.

32:13.313 --> 32:15.048
I UNDERSTAND.

32:20.353 --> 32:22.656
THANK YOU, JEFFERY.

32:22.656 --> 32:23.790
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

32:23.790 --> 32:25.826
I'LL SEE YOU LATER,
MRS. CRYER.

32:54.788 --> 32:56.790
WYATT.

32:56.790 --> 32:58.124
HEY.

32:58.124 --> 33:00.026
HEY. HOW ARE YOU?

33:00.026 --> 33:02.302
UH, ALL RIGHT.

33:02.302 --> 33:04.104
JEFFERY.

33:06.072 --> 33:07.608
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

33:10.544 --> 33:12.245
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

33:13.880 --> 33:15.516
GO ON UPSTAIRS
AND GET CLEANED UP, COME ON.

33:15.516 --> 33:17.483
NOT BEFORE I TAKE
A LOOK AT YOU.

33:19.986 --> 33:21.655
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

33:26.426 --> 33:28.261
GO ON.

33:28.261 --> 33:29.530
BUT COME RIGHT BACK.

33:29.530 --> 33:31.464
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
SOME DINNER, OKAY?

33:31.464 --> 33:33.099
ALL RIGHT.

33:42.175 --> 33:43.877
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

33:43.877 --> 33:45.245
Katheryn: THANK YOU.

33:45.245 --> 33:47.948
FOR BRINGING HIM BACK TO ME.

33:47.948 --> 33:51.084
HE'S MY SON, TOO.

33:51.084 --> 33:52.919
IS THIS GOING TO WORK, JIM?

33:52.919 --> 33:56.523
THERE'S MORE TO IT, KATHERYN.
ANOTHER PIECE TO THE PUZZLE.

33:56.523 --> 33:58.424
AND THAT WOULD
MAKE IT WORK?

33:58.424 --> 34:00.894
I SURE HOPE SO.

34:00.894 --> 34:02.603
I NEED YOU
TO BE MORE THAN SURE, JIM.

34:02.603 --> 34:03.637
I'M DOING THE BEST I CAN

34:03.637 --> 34:05.205
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
KATHERYN.

34:05.205 --> 34:07.641
IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,
I'VE BEEN A LITTLE BUSY LATELY.

34:07.641 --> 34:10.043
OH, GOOD. BECAUSE NOW
WE HAVE ANOTHER PROBLEM.

34:10.043 --> 34:11.111
REALLY? WHAT'S THAT?

34:11.111 --> 34:12.445
AMANDA BOUGHT A GUN.

34:13.747 --> 34:15.782
HOW IN THE HELL DID AMANDA
BUY A GUN?

34:15.782 --> 34:19.152
HOW DOES ANY INSANE PERSON
IN THIS COUNTRY BUY A GUN, JIM?

34:19.152 --> 34:21.522
THEY JUST WALK IN THE STORE
AND BUY ONE.

34:22.756 --> 34:24.424
AND THAT'S WHY JEFFERY
WAS HERE?

34:24.424 --> 34:27.628
YES. TO TELL US THAT, AND THE
FACT THAT SHE'S BECOME A DANGER,

34:27.628 --> 34:29.462
NOT ONLY
TO HERSELF AND OTHERS.

34:32.365 --> 34:34.935
ALL RIGHT, I'LL GO TALK
TO HER TOMORROW.

34:34.935 --> 34:36.136
DAMN IT.

34:37.938 --> 34:39.573
SHE SHOULD BE COMMITTED.

34:39.573 --> 34:41.107
NO.

34:41.107 --> 34:43.944
JIM, SHE NEEDS TO BE.

34:43.944 --> 34:46.246
THIS IS SERIOUS.

34:46.246 --> 34:47.313
OH, REALLY?

34:47.313 --> 34:48.815
KATHERYN, THANK YOU
FOR ENLIGHTENING ME.

34:48.815 --> 34:50.483
I DIDN'T REALIZE
THIS WAS SERIOUS.

34:50.483 --> 34:52.318
SHE'S NOT GOING
TO BE COMMITTED, OKAY?

34:52.318 --> 34:53.353
NOT AGAIN.

34:53.353 --> 34:55.121
WHAT ABOUT HER THREATS?

34:55.121 --> 34:56.122
WHAT THREATS?

34:56.122 --> 34:57.190
TO KILL ALL OF US.

34:57.190 --> 34:59.125
OH, COME ON, KATHERYN.

34:59.125 --> 35:00.460
REALLY?

35:00.460 --> 35:03.203
I'LL TALK TO HER AND SEE
WHERE SHE IS.

35:03.203 --> 35:04.437
OKAY?

35:04.437 --> 35:06.673
I'LL GET DR. LISTON
TO COME BY WHILE SHE'S HERE.

35:06.673 --> 35:08.474
SHE SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

35:08.474 --> 35:10.110
SHE IS OUR DAUGHTER.

35:10.110 --> 35:12.879
WHO'S HAVING A MENTAL BREAKDOWN
AND WHO NEEDS SOME ‐‐

35:12.879 --> 35:15.381
I'M NOT GOING TO HAVE
OUR DAUGHTER COMMITTED AGAIN!

35:15.381 --> 35:16.983
YOU NEVER LISTEN TO ME.

35:16.983 --> 35:18.619
I NEVER LISTEN TO YOU,
YOU NEVER LISTEN TO ME,

35:18.619 --> 35:20.120
AND THAT'S GOOD BECAUSE
IT MAKES US EVEN.

35:20.120 --> 35:21.555
BUT, JIM ‐‐

35:21.555 --> 35:24.390
THE LAST TIME THIS HAPPENED, SHE
HAD A BREAKDOWN FOR A REASON.

35:24.390 --> 35:26.760
IT STANDS TO REASON THAT
SOMETHING HAS GONE WRONG.

35:26.760 --> 35:28.629
I'LL FIND OUT WHAT IT IS.
I'LL FIX IT.

35:28.629 --> 35:29.963
AND HOW ARE YOU GOING
TO DO THAT?

35:29.963 --> 35:31.364
THERE IS ONE PERSON
ON THIS PLANET

35:31.364 --> 35:32.733
THAT KNOWS EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED.

35:32.733 --> 35:34.901
NINE?

35:34.901 --> 35:37.538
YES. NINE.

35:37.538 --> 35:39.439
I WILL TALK TO HER
AND I WILL FIND OUT

35:39.439 --> 35:42.175
EXACTLY WHAT HAPPENED WITH
OUR DAUGHTER SO I CAN HELP HER.

35:42.175 --> 35:44.711
SO, YOU'RE JUST GOING
TO GO SEE NINE?

35:46.813 --> 35:49.750
NINE IS NO LONGER A PROBLEM,
KATHERYN.

35:49.750 --> 35:50.751
AND HOW IS THAT?

35:50.751 --> 35:52.018
I HANDLED IT.

35:52.018 --> 35:53.486
REALLY?

35:53.486 --> 35:56.757
HOW DID YOU HANDLE IT?

35:56.757 --> 35:59.459
I HANDLED IT.

36:01.668 --> 36:04.170
YOU HAD BETTER.

36:18.351 --> 36:20.386
YOU WANT SOME WATER?

36:20.386 --> 36:22.689
NO.

36:25.158 --> 36:26.226
PRETTY GIRL.

36:26.226 --> 36:29.029
HOW DID YOU GET CAUGHT UP
IN THIS MESS?

36:29.029 --> 36:31.164
I DON'T KNOW.

36:31.164 --> 36:34.601
EVERYBODY'S GOT A STORY.

36:34.601 --> 36:36.436
I WAS BORN INTO THIS.

36:36.436 --> 36:38.705
MY FATHER WAS A CRIME BOSS.

36:38.705 --> 36:40.974
AND HIS FATHER BEFORE THAT.

36:40.974 --> 36:42.976
I DIDN'T HAVE ANY BROTHERS,

36:42.976 --> 36:45.979
SO IT WAS KIND
OF PASSED ON DOWN TO ME.

36:45.979 --> 36:50.250
I HAD A LOT TO PROVE,
AS MOST WOMEN DO.

36:50.250 --> 36:53.453
YOU GOT A LOT TO PROVE?

36:53.453 --> 36:57.991
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
TO PROVE.

36:57.991 --> 36:59.926
SO, WHAT ARE
YOU GOING TO DO?

36:59.926 --> 37:02.501
ABOUT WHAT?

37:02.501 --> 37:05.171
WHAT HE ASKED YOU TO DO.

37:05.171 --> 37:06.573
[ SCOFFS ]

37:06.573 --> 37:08.374
NEVER MIND.

37:08.374 --> 37:09.909
[ SIGHS ]

37:11.477 --> 37:17.300
THE LONGER YOU HOLD OUT,
THE COLDER HE GETS.

37:17.751 --> 37:20.253
YOU KNOW?

37:20.253 --> 37:21.888
HE'S DANGEROUS, YOU KNOW?

37:23.624 --> 37:25.992
YEAH, YOU THINK
YOU'RE JUST DEALING

37:25.992 --> 37:31.698
WITH SOMEONE THAT'S
RICH, LUCKY...

37:31.698 --> 37:33.700
[ LAUGHS ]

37:33.700 --> 37:35.669
HE'S THE DEVIL.

37:36.603 --> 37:39.906
AND HE LOVES HIS CHILDREN.

37:42.042 --> 37:44.144
I'M NOT SCARED OF HIM.

37:44.144 --> 37:46.813
[ SIGHS ]

37:46.813 --> 37:48.882
THAT IS SO STUPID.

37:48.882 --> 37:50.584
YOU SHOULD BE.

37:56.289 --> 37:59.125
I'M NOT GOING TO LET HIM
WALK ALL OVER ME.

38:00.834 --> 38:02.936
SO FUNNY.

38:02.936 --> 38:07.007
YOU DON'T WANT
TO BE WALKED ON?

38:07.007 --> 38:09.042
THAT'S WHY THERE'S
THIS BOX.

38:10.376 --> 38:13.313
I'M PRETTY SURE
HE'S GOING TO KILL YOU.

38:13.313 --> 38:15.516
I MEAN, HE CALLED US TODAY

38:15.516 --> 38:18.585
AND ASKED US
TO "PREPARE THE BOX."

38:18.585 --> 38:21.087
WHAT'S THE BOX?

38:21.087 --> 38:22.989
SEE OVER THERE?

38:22.989 --> 38:27.227
IT'S PLASTIC, LIME, CEMENT.

38:27.227 --> 38:29.029
WHAT DO YOU THINK
THAT'S FOR, HONEY?

38:30.931 --> 38:34.200
AND I'M BUTCHER.

38:34.200 --> 38:36.603
YOU PREPARED TO DIE?

38:36.603 --> 38:38.872
OH, NEVER MIND.

38:38.872 --> 38:40.473
[ SIGHS ]

38:40.473 --> 38:43.443
YOU PEOPLE NEVER ARE.

38:43.443 --> 38:47.280
YOU THINK YOU CAN DO THINGS
TO PEOPLE AND GET AWAY WITH IT.

38:47.280 --> 38:48.949
[ SCOFFS ]

38:48.949 --> 38:52.052
THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN,
YOU'RE DOWN HERE

38:52.052 --> 38:53.353
WITH ME.

38:53.353 --> 38:57.157
AND PRETTY SOON,
YOU'RE IN A CEMENT BLOCK

38:57.157 --> 39:00.934
IN THE FOUNDATION
OF A NEW BUILDING.

39:00.934 --> 39:02.936
SPECIAL BUILDING,

39:02.936 --> 39:08.474
WHERE MILLIONS OF PEOPLE ARE
WALKING ALL OVER YOU ALL DAY.

39:11.444 --> 39:12.813
YOU'RE PRETTY.

39:12.813 --> 39:14.414
BUT YOU'RE STUPID.

39:17.483 --> 39:18.952
I'D...

39:18.952 --> 39:21.421
ASK YOU WHAT YOU WANT
FOR YOUR LAST MEAL...

39:24.124 --> 39:27.127
BUT WHAT'S THE POINT?

39:50.884 --> 39:52.452
HEY, DARLENE.
HEY.

39:52.452 --> 39:53.820
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
OFF BY NOW.

39:53.820 --> 39:57.123
I AM, BUT I KNOW HIS MOM AND SHE
ASKED ME TO SIT WITH HIM.

39:57.123 --> 39:58.559
OH, OKAY.

39:58.559 --> 39:59.826
YEAH.
SO, HOW'S HE DOING?

39:59.826 --> 40:02.636
WELL, BREATHING ON HIS OWN.

40:02.636 --> 40:03.837
YEAH.

40:03.837 --> 40:05.271
YEAH.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

40:05.271 --> 40:06.740
ALL RIGHT.

40:09.943 --> 40:11.578
HEY.

40:11.578 --> 40:13.179
HOW'S HE DOING?

40:13.179 --> 40:14.447
DOING GOOD.

40:14.447 --> 40:16.382
THANK YOU FOR KEEPING
AN EYE ON HIM.

40:16.382 --> 40:18.284
I DID.

40:18.284 --> 40:20.954
HEY.
HAS HE MOVED ANY?

40:20.954 --> 40:24.224
NO, BUT HE WAS BLINKING
HIS EYES EARLIER.

40:24.224 --> 40:25.659
WAS HE?
YES.

40:25.659 --> 40:28.294
OH, YES. [ LAUGHS ]

40:28.294 --> 40:29.596
HANNA?

40:29.596 --> 40:30.931
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

40:30.931 --> 40:31.965
I FOLLOWED YOU.

40:31.965 --> 40:33.133
GET OUT OF HERE, TONY.

40:33.133 --> 40:35.435
LOOK AT HIM JUST LAYING THERE,
STILL THE SAME.

40:35.435 --> 40:36.469
YOU ARE WRONG FOR THIS.

40:36.469 --> 40:37.504
HE IS DOING BETTER.

40:37.504 --> 40:39.005
HE'S THE SAME, HANNA.

40:39.005 --> 40:41.508
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE, TONY.

40:41.508 --> 40:42.909
I ALREADY TALKED TO
MY LAWYER.

40:42.909 --> 40:44.745
HE'S ON HIS WAY RIGHT NOW
TO THE JUDGE

40:44.745 --> 40:45.946
TO HAVE THIS RULING DONE.

40:45.946 --> 40:47.113
HE'S COMING HERE TODAY.

40:47.113 --> 40:48.414
OVER MY DEAD BODY, HE WILL.

40:48.414 --> 40:49.950
YOU'RE JUST MAKING
THINGS WORSE.

40:49.950 --> 40:51.618
TONY, HE IS BETTER.

40:51.618 --> 40:52.753
WELL, IT'S TOO LATE.

40:52.753 --> 40:53.787
GET OUT OF HERE.

40:53.787 --> 40:54.788
HANNA ‐‐

40:54.788 --> 40:55.789
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

40:55.789 --> 40:57.090
YES.
I'LL CALL SECURITY.

40:57.090 --> 40:58.291
PLEASE.

40:58.291 --> 41:00.460
YEAH, YOU DO THAT, BECAUSE
I'VE GOT A COURT ORDER

41:00.460 --> 41:02.002
TO HAVE HIM TAKEN OFF
LIFE SUPPORT.

41:02.002 --> 41:03.937
YOU ARE NOT TOUCHING MY SON.

41:03.937 --> 41:05.105
HE'S BRAIN‐DEAD.

41:05.105 --> 41:06.607
HE IS NOT!
CAN'T YOU SEE?!

41:06.607 --> 41:08.942
HE'S DOING BETTER.
HE'S BREATHING ON HIS OWN.

41:08.942 --> 41:09.976
I'M NOT PLAYING.

41:09.976 --> 41:12.112
I AIN'T PLAYING
WITH YOU, EITHER!

41:12.112 --> 41:13.547
JUST GO ON
TALKING ABOUT MY MAMA...

41:13.547 --> 41:14.948
OH, BABY!

41:14.948 --> 41:15.949
BABY?

41:15.949 --> 41:18.985
I HEARD HIM SAY SOMETHING.

41:18.985 --> 41:20.186
WHAT'D YOU SAY?

41:20.186 --> 41:21.955
NURSE! NURSE!

41:21.955 --> 41:24.891
NURSE!
SAY SOMETHING ELSE, BABY.

41:24.891 --> 41:28.328
SAY SOMETHING ELSE.
I HEARD YOU.

41:31.131 --> 41:33.834
<i>NEXT ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:33.834 --> 41:35.569
WHAT'S YOUR LIFE LIKE?

41:35.569 --> 41:37.738
EXCUSE ME?

41:37.738 --> 41:39.573
I MEAN, BEING GAY.

41:39.573 --> 41:41.141
WHAT DID I ASK YOU FOR?

41:41.141 --> 41:43.476
JIM, NO!
JIM!

41:43.476 --> 41:45.345
HOW'S YOUR BED HAIR?

41:45.345 --> 41:48.849
UH...FINE.

41:48.849 --> 41:50.717
YOU EVER HAD AN AFFAIR?

41:50.717 --> 41:52.853
SHE NEVER MENTIONED
A SON.

41:52.853 --> 41:55.055
I'M HER BABY'S FATHER.

41:55.055 --> 41:57.390
SHE'S BEEN HOLDING OUT ON ME.

41:57.390 --> 41:59.660
BENNY? NURSE!
